result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI Cause Injury (2+) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI Cause Injury (2+) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Margaret M Starr was found guilty of OWI Cause Injury (2+), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.
  • Margaret M Starr was found guilty of Knowingly Operating While Revoked (Cause Great Bodily Harm), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

supervisions.notes: If a Wisconsin State Prison sentence is imposed, outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all inmate money at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.
